deck_excerpt: Laval Judgment Lord FTK ft. Primal Seed+Different Dimension
deck_description:
Welcome! In this deck, we will place Laval Lord back and forth between Graveyard (GY) and Banish Zone (BZ) to FTK our opponent. Let me tell you how.

 

 

Gameplan

1) Throughout the game, either discard one or two copies of "Laval Judgment Lord". You can achieve it with Dugares/Ravenous.

2) After ME-PSY-YA has been placed on Pendulum Zone, Special Summon "Chaos Emperor Dragon". It's needed to find and cycle combo pieces with "Primal Seed", as long as you target Primal Seeds each other.

3) Special Summon Laval Lord, either with "Monster Reborn" or Saryuja.

4) With Laval Lord present on the battlefield, banish other Laval Lord to deal 1000 damage.

5) Return banished Laval Lord with "Burial from a Different Dimension".

6) Destroy Laval Lord with "Offerings to the Doomed" and revive it with "Monster Reborn".

7) Rinse and repeat what was explained in #4 + #5 + #6, while dealing 1000 damage constantly, until your opponent is dead.

 

If you wonder how to save up some SR and UR points, I can show you:

- "Monster Reborn" is given for free, if you have completed the tutorial to save 30 UR!

- "Pot of Avarice" can be collected by purchasing "Re-Contract Universe" deck. 90 SR saved and you can try a new deck!

- "Ravenous" + "Primal Seed" + "Pot of Acquisitiveness" can be found within "Legacy Pack" to save 60 SR and 60 UR!

- "Number 60: Dugares the Timeless" can be found within "Number Recall" Secret Pack to save 30 SR!

- "Into The Void" + "Allure of Darkness" can be found within "The Infinite Void" Secret Pack to save 180 SR!

- "Formula Synchron" can be found within "Stardust Ties" Secret Pack to save 90 SR!

- "T.G. Hyper Librarian" can be found within "Futuristic Creatures" Secret Pack to save 30 UR!

- "Wonder Wand" and "Spellbook of Knowledge" can be collected by purchasing "Spellbook of Prophecy" deck. 120 SR saved and you can try a new deck!

 

So, in total, you can save up to 570 SR and 120 UR, if you are willing to spend some gems. Other SR and UR cards I didn't mention are essential.

 

That's all for this one. If you have any questions, feel free to ask. Have fun in Master Duel!

¡El mago oscuro es un arquetipo que ha sido parte de Yu-Gi-Oh! franquicia desde sus inicios, con "Dark Magician" apareciendo como la carta estrella de Yugi Muto. Durante el arco de Battle City y los arcos posteriores, se introdujeron más cartas, como "Dark Magician Girl". Originalmente una serie, el lanzamiento de "El ojo de Timeo" consolidó su estatus como arquetipo. Albaz Dragon es una serie de Monstruos de Fusión OSCUROS o LIGROS de Nivel 8 que mencionan "Caído de Albaz" como Material de Fusión. Comparten un esquema de nombres similar y la mayoría de ellos tienen 2500 ATK y 2000 DEF. La serie se apoya indirectamente en el arquetipo "Branded" y temas relacionados. Branded es un arquetipo introducido en Lightning Overdrive. Este arquetipo está relacionado por la tradición con "Fallen of Albaz" y los monstruos que lo apoyan específicamente, y algunos miembros también apoyan directamente los arquetipos "Despia" y "Bystial". TRASLATE: Dark magician is an archetype that has been a part of the Yu-Gi-Oh! franchise since its beginning, with "Dark Magician" appearing as Yugi Muto's ace card. During the Battle City arc and subsequent arcs, more cards were introduced, such as "Dark Magician Girl". Originally a series, the release of "The Eye of Timaeus" cemented its status as an archetype. Albaz Dragon is a series of Level 8 DARK or LIGHT Fusion Monsters that mention "Fallen of Albaz" as a Fusion Material. They share a similar naming scheme, and the majority of them have 2500 ATK and 2000 DEF. The series is indirectly supported by the "Branded" archetype and related themes. Branded is an archetype introduced in Lightning Overdrive. This archetype is related by lore to "Fallen of Albaz" and monsters that specifically support it, with some members also directly supporting the "Despia" and "Bystial" archetypes. deck_excerpt: Abuse Rescue-Ace combos to obliterate your opponent and accrue massive value
deck_description:
You know here's the transcript for the first section of the Youtube video linked.

"Todays deck profile is for the meta threat Rescue Ace. After a poor showing on release, it’s most recent support has thrust this deck into the modern yugioh game. This profile will be covering every build of Rescue Ace. Although the video will be leading with the Iblee Lock version of Rescue Ace. After explaining basic combos and showing off the deck list we will get into other builds such a go second staple list, Cyberse and Terahertz lists, Superheavy Samurai Rescue Ace, Infernoble knight rescue ace as well as a few others. I will also go into how to use the future Diabellstar support at the end of the video. If you want more resources on how to play the deck, I recommend checking out the links in the description below. It has everything from a Combo sheet, to various topping deck profiles, to the Rescue ace discord who have been very helpful in aiding me with this profile.

We can break down the general game plan of Rescue Ace into three main points. First we should look to combo out with Hydrant, Air Lifter, or Emergency. This means using Rescue Ace Turbulence’s set 4 plus whatever extra deck shenanigans the build is running. Second we have amazing tools to hand trap the opponent. Not only with generic staples but also with Rescue Ace Impulse which tributes itself from hand as a quick effect to fetch us any Rescue Ace from the deck. This can be as simple as Rescue ACE Fire Attacker for some quick draws or something like Rescue Ace Fire engine into Air Lifter or Hydrant for some hand fixing.

If you want a more board breaking build consider replacing some staples with You choice of board breakers. Kurikawa, Dark Ruler, and Harpie’s Feather Duster come to mind. Lastly the deck ensures wins through it’s absurd grind game. Fire Attacker and Decode Talker Heatsoul put a lot of cards into your hand. Rescue Ace HQ is a complete reset and draw after you first Turbulence effect. And all of the other Rescue Ace effects are still really good at grinding.

It is also important to remember that Rescue Ace’s strategy inherently loses to blowout cards such as Lighting Storm, Harpies Feather Duster, and especially Evenly Matched. As such each build seeks to counteract this in it’s own unique way. Iblee builds give an opponent a card to lock out opponent’s from the effects, Cyberse establishes a spell/trap negate through Cyberse Desavewurm, and Rank 4 builds establish An omninegate through Therion King Regulus.

 

<!-- [if !supportLists]-->·       <!--[endif]-->EMERGECNY + Monster Combos

<!-- [if !supportLists]-->o   <!--[endif]-->Standard Turbulence Set 4

So lets get into combos with the basic Turbulence set up. Emergency and any Rescue Ace monster will let us summon Rescue Ace Hydrant from the deck. Hydrant will then let us search Rescue Ace Turbulence. Turbulence can then banish out two cards in graveyard for his special summon, then turbulence get’s his set 4 from the deck. There are options for what to set but typically it’ll be CONTAIN, EXTINGUISH, and RESCUE for disruptions. As well as ALERT for extension.

<!-- [if !supportLists]-->o   <!--[endif]-->IP:Masqueana + Set 4

We can levy this previous set up into more disruptions, by using the ALERT we set to search Rescue Ace Preventer. Hydrant lets us activate it the turn it was set. We can then summon Preventer by banishing the alert. Then we can link off the Turbulence and Preventer into IP:Masquerna. Typically this helps somewhat for playing around evenly, since we can condense our board with Apollosa if they try to go to battle phase. But it also gives use access to Knightmare Unicore for flexible removal. You don’t have to condense the board if you think Preventer + Turbulence would be more helpful

 

<!-- [if !supportLists]-->·       <!--[endif]-->Rescue Ace Hydrant Combos

<!-- [if !supportLists]-->o   <!--[endif]-->Decode Talker Heatsoul

With just a Rescue Ace Hydrant in hand out combos get a bit more limited. The combo you’re likely to do here is to make Decode Talker Heatsoul. Normal summon Hydrant. Use Hydrant to search Prventer. Link Hydrant off into Salamangreat A’lumiraj. Banish Hydrant to summon Preventer. Link Preventer Plus Alumiraj into Salamangreat Sunlight Wulf. Use Preventer’s when sent to graveyard effect to revive Hydrant from banish zone. Summon Hydrant In Sunlight Wulf’s zone to add Preventer back to hand. Link off Hydrant into Linkuriboh. Link Sunlight Wulf and Linkuriboh into Heatsoul. Then you have an extra draw to try and find a hand trap or some way to unbrick. 

Decode Talker Heatsoul is a very important option because he’s so easy to make. You can make it off emergency and any Rescue Ace monster or just an Air Lifter. Heatsoul plays into the grind game aspect of the deck and is benefited by how many hand traps builds run.

 

<!-- [if !supportLists]-->·       <!--[endif]-->Rescue Ace Air Lifter Combos

<!-- [if !supportLists]-->o   <!--[endif]-->Decode Talker Heatsoul

Here’s the Just Airlifter line for Heatsoul. Airlifter search Emergency. Use emergency to summon Hydrant tributing Airlifter. Use Hydrant to search Turbulence. Turbulence banishing grave to summon him. Have turbulence set the 4 main cards. CONTAIN, EXTINGUSIH, RESCUE, and ALERT. Activate alert using Hydrant and search Preventer. Summon Preventer banishing ALERT. Link Preventer and Turbulence to make Salamangreat Sunlight Wulf. Special Airlifter using Preventer’s when sent to graveyard effect. Link Hydrant into Linkuribo. Link Linkuriboh and Sunlight Wulf into Decode Talker Heatsoul.

So using Turbulence as a base to go into Preventer we can realistically do an absurd amount of combos. Building of this we can even summon Iblee from the deck off of one card.

<!-- [if !supportLists]-->o   <!--[endif]-->Iblee Lock

<!-- [if !supportLists]-->§  <!--[endif]-->Do note that this combo is possible with just hydrant in builds running Binary sorceress and G Golem crystal heart

Airlifter search Emergency. Use emergency to summon Hydrant tributing Airlifter. Use Hydrant to search Turbulence. Turbulence banishing grave to summon him. Have turbulence set the 4 main cards. CONTAIN, EXTINGUSIH, RESCUE, and ALERT. Activate alert using Hydrant and search Preventer. Summon Preventer banishing ALERT. Now here’s the difference. Link summon into Puzzlomino the Drop and Deleter and then use Preventer to summon back Airlifter to the zone Puzzlomino points to. Use Puzzlomino’s effect to change Airlifter’s level to two. Overlay Puzzlomino and Airlifter into Gigantic Spright. Use Gigantic Spright to summon Knightmare Conductor Iblee from the deck. Link Iblee and Gigantic Spright into Beat Cop from the Underworld. Activate Iblee’s effect when use as link material to send it to the opponent’s field. Lastly use Beat Cop’s effect to put a token on the Iblee. This will protect it from destruction once.

So here we have a special summon lock that can’t be outed by a singular destruction and it prevents Lighting Storm and Evenly Matched. You can see why I favor this build.

 

<!-- [if !supportLists]-->·       <!--[endif]-->Hydrant + Preventer / Air Lifter + Emergency

<!-- [if !supportLists]-->o   <!--[endif]-->Mudragon + Turbulence

The last major combo is how to make Mudragon of the Swamp in order to give targeting protection to Turbulence. This is important because some players will wait out your plays to go for it. Mudragon forces this out.

Thes easiest way to get to this combo is through Air Lifter and Preventer. Summon Airlifter then search Emergency. Use emergency to summon Hydrant tributing Airlifter. Use Hydrant to search Turbulence. This time we’re going to lead with Preventer. Summon Preventer Banishing Air Lifter. Link summon Proxy F. Magician using Hydrant and Preventer. Use Preventer’s effect in grave to summon back Air Lifter. Use Proxy F. Magician’s effect to fusion summon into Mudragon using both it and Air Lifter. Activate Mudragon changing himself to fire type. Now you can summon Rescue Ace Turbulence from hand without fear of being Infinite Impermanence’d.

This combo can also be done with Preventer and Hydrant, as well as with Air Lifter and EMERGENCY. You have a ton of options with this one. Just understand it takes a good player to figure out when to play it safe with Mudragon vs when to extend with Iblee lock.

 

<!-- [if !supportLists]-->·       <!--[endif]-->Deck List

My deck list is a bit of a middle ground as far as Rescue Ace builds go. I’m running the standard core. Which you can see here. 3 of every starter, 2 each of the combo extenders, and 1 each of out hand trap extenders as well as out search targets. In the extra deck, which is where most of the spice comes from, I’m running the Iblee Lock package, the Heatsoul Package, and the Mudragon package. TBH though the Heatsoul package is basically generic to most Rescue Ace Builds.

My main deck is the filled up with with 3 Ash blossom and 3 Infinite impermance. Along with Resuce Ace Impulse this brings us up to 9 hand traps. Good odds to draw off of Heatsoul or just in general. Especially after setting 4 cards from deck and doing our combos.

I’m also running 3 Book of Eclipse and 3 Book of Moon. Board breaking is tough and these cards are excellent this format and in general to be honest.

This build has amazing power, great combos and fantastic flexibility as we can se from the before mentioned combo’s. This builds weaknesses should be noted. First up is consistency. It has only 10 guaranteed starters which gets bumped up to about 15 with some cards working conditionally. I haven’t had that much of a problem with it, but it wouldn’t be a bad call to take out the Called by the Grave and throw in 3 Pot of Prosperity.

Second this build can still struggle with blowouts. If you play to timidly you will be vulnerable. Use you judgement and create boards to deal deal with an oppoen’ts likely options. Make Iblee lock when you can. Make IP:Masquenra to conduse boards. And use REINFORCE to try not neg as hard on value. It will be rough, but you have the tools to fix it.

 

<!-- [if !supportLists]-->·       <!--[endif]-->Side Deck

I’m not going to go in depth on side deck options, but I recommend putting in at least Droll and Lock bird as well as Nibiru.

If you’re going first you can side out two copies of impulse and even potentially Fire Engine. Mostly though you’ll be changing out the disruptions and hand traps that don’t work in a specific match up. Like Book of Eclipse or Infinite Impermanence. I recommend following current trends for side decking."
Pure Majespecter Post Phantom Nightmare
Tearlaments Ishuzu Kashtira

deck_name: Raidraptors for Monster Type Festival: King of the Island
deck_excerpt: Going second Raidraptor deck for the festival
deck_description:
This deck requires 15 SR and 5 UR non-staples, so it's a bit on the expensive side. However there is some room for changing out some of those.

 

Here's my reasoning for the inclusion of the individual cards:

Staples:

Maxx "C" : Does this card really need an explanation? This is a going second deck, more cards in hand is always better, enough said.

Raigeki : Clean up those pesky monsters on your opponents side of the field, can be easily replaced with lightning storm.

Harpie's Feather Duster : Clean up those pesky spells/traps on your opponents side of the field, can be easily replaced with lightning storm.

Crossout Designator : Prevent Infinite Impermanence , Called by the Grave on your turn and sometimes even Raigeki and Harpie's Feather Duster , assuming you haven't used them up yet, on your opponents turn from ruining your day.

Infinite Impermanence : Timed right, this thing stops opponents boards before they can happen.

 

Main Deck Cards:

Raidraptor - Pain Lanius : Free special summon, as long as you control any other Raidraptor monster. Should only be used on lvl 4 monsters, but can be used in emergencies for link material for Raidraptor - Wise Strix .

Raidraptor - Heel Eagle : Free special summon, as long as you control any other Raidraptor monster. Link material for Raidraptor - Wise Strix . Graveyard effect is useful to recycle Raidraptor - Call or Raidraptor - Nest .

Raidraptor - Mimicry Lanius : Best target to send to GY with Raidraptor - Tribute Lanius , since its GY effect can search half your deck. Depending on your hand and field you can add Raider's Wing , Raidraptor - Fuzzy Lanius, Raidraptor - Strangle Lanius , Raidraptor - Pain Lanius or Raidraptor - Heel Eagle  for some free special summons or Raidraptor - Nest to search with it, provided your field already has 2 Raidraptors. In rare cases used to increase the level of your monsters to 5 and go into Raidraptor - Blaze Falcon directly.

Raidraptor - Tribute Lanius : Best card to normal summon or special summon with Swallow's Nest . Send either Raidraptor - Mimicry Lanius for a free search or Raidraptor - Fuzzy Lanius to get another Raidraptor - Fuzzy Lanius to your hand. In extremely rare cases you could also send Raidraptor - Heel Eagle to recover Raidraptor - Nest or Raidraptor - Call .

Raidraptor - Fuzzy Lanius : Free special summon, as long as you control any other Raidraptor monster, and adds another one to your hand if send to the GY (also works when detached as XYZ material).

Raidraptor - Singing Lanius : Good card to add to your hand with Raidraptor - Force Strix , since then you can immediately special summon it to the field.

Raidraptor - Necro Vulture : Highly optional card, can be replaced with another Raidraptor - Fuzzy Lanius for example. Normally used to tribute itself to recover a rank-up spell, only really useful if the game goes on for a while or if you special summon it with Raidraptor - Arsenal Falcon to recover the rank-up spell you used to get it out in the first place.

Raider's Wing : Good card to special summon with Raidraptor - Wise Strix , since the protection part for the XYZ monster that has it as material and its GY effect are the most interesting parts about it and those are of course not affected by the negation of its effect on field.

Raidraptor - Strangle Lanius : Free special summon, as long as you control any other Raidraptor monster. Really good card to search with Raidraptor - Force Strix , while Raidraptor - Wise Strix is on filed since after you use the rank-up spell Raidraptor - Wise Strix searches on Raidraptor - Force Strix you can use Raidraptor - Strangle Lanius  on field effect to special summon another monster from your GY.

Rank-Up-Magic Raid Force : Used to either turn one of your rank 4s into Raidraptor - Blaze Falcon to blow up your opponents monster (since they probably control only, or at least mostly special summoned monsters) or to turn one of your rank 6s into Raidraptor - Arsenal Falcon to go for game.

Raidraptor - Call : Duplicate one of your monsters on field.

Rank-Up-Magic Skip Force : Turn your Raidraptor - Force Strix into a Raidraptor - Revolution Falcon to pop a monster on your opponents side of the field and inflict some burn damage. Or turn one of your rank 6s into Raidraptor - Satellite Cannon Falcon to get rid of your opponents spells/traps.

Wing Requital : Since you're basically always going to have 2 or more winged beasts and only winged beasts on your field this is just a pot of greed.

Raidraptor - Nest : Since you're basically always going to have 2 or more Raidraptors on your field this is just a free search. Can be searched with Raidraptor - Mimicry Lanius . Can also recycle cards from the GY back to your hand or extra deck.

Swallow's Nest : Turn one of your lvl 4 monsters into Raidraptor - Tribute Lanius to get your combos started or in incredibly rare cases into Raidraptor - Necro Vulture to recover a rank up spell, or Raidraptor - Mimicry Lanius to increase your monsters levels by 1. Also provides some protection against targeting effects like Infinite Impermanence for your lvl 4 monsters.

Phantom Knights' Rank-Up-Magic Force : Can be used on your opponents turn to go into Raidraptor - Revolution Falcon - Air Raid to destroy a monster or Raidraptor - Satellite Cannon Falcon , to blow up their backrow, for some disruption or to go into basically your whole extra deck, provided you have enough stuff in your GY. In most cases you won't have enough to go into Raidraptor - Final Fortress Falcon so you don't need to save up this card to try and go into it later (especially since the GY effect of Raidraptor - Arsenal Falcon can special summon it with its protection live anyway). Also provides some protection against targeting effects like Infinite Impermanence for your XYZ monsters.

Xyz Align : Highly optional card. Mainly used to go into Raidraptor - Satellite Cannon Falcon to blow up backrow or in some rare cases into Raidraptor - Final Fortress Falcon to recycle your banished cards back to your GY ( Raidraptor - Final Fortress Falcon won't have its protection then, since it doesn't have an XYZ monster as material).

Extra Deck:

Raidraptor - Rise Falcon : Can single-handedly win you the game if your opponent leaves out multiple weak special summoned monsters in attack mode and one strong monster. The ATK gain is permanent. Rarely happens though, but incredibly satisfying if it does.

Raidraptor - Force Strix : The card you'll be summoning the most often. Its search is only a soft once per turn so if you bring it out multiple times you can search multiple times. Use a rank-up magic on it after you've searched to get one of your other extra deck monsters depending on board state.

Raidraptor - Blade Burner Falcon : Incredibly situational, probably the card you'll summon the least and is mainly only there to be able to bring out another 2 material rank 4 to rank up on, in case all your Raidraptor - Force Strix have already been used.

Raidraptor - Blaze Falcon : Lets you blow up all of your opponents special summoned monster. An extra pop for normal summoned ones during the battle phase.

Raidraptor - Stranger Falcon : A free targeted monster destruction with some good burn damage. Since you most likely brought it out by ranking up, it will have another XYZ monster attached which it can special summon from the grave in case it gets destroyed.

Raidraptor - Revolution Falcon : A free targeted monster destruction with some minor burn damage. Can beat over any special summoned monster, as long as it's not just plain unaffected by everything, and its ATK/DEF reduction doesn't target. Also the ATK/DEF reduction applies also when it is being attacked. (also notice the lack of "until the end of the turn" with the ATK/DEF reduction).

Raidraptor - Revolution Falcon - Air Raid : Good card to bring out on your opponents turn with Phantom Knights' Rank-Up-Magic Force to destroy one of their monsters. Floats into Raidraptor - Revolution Falcon on destruction.

Raidraptor - Arsenal Falcon : Can special summon anything from your deck without negating that cards effects. Floats into Raidraptor - Final Fortress Falcon with its protection active on destruction. Can easily inflict 7500 or sometimes even 10000 points of damage with direct attacks, since its "attack as many times as it has materials" doesn't specify "on monsters" and it can be easily brought out with 3 materials by ranking it up once on Raidraptor - Force Strix with Phantom Knights' Rank-Up-Magic Force or twice on Raidraptor - Force Strix with a combination of either 2 different ones of the rank-up spells, while either destroying all special summoned monsters if Raidraptor - Blaze Falcon was your stepping stone (you'll lose one material then) or only one monster with Raidraptor - Revolution Falcon or Raidraptor - Revolution Falcon - Air Raid without losing material.

Raidraptor - Satellite Cannon Falcon : Brought out either by ranking up or going into it with Xyz Align . Destroys all of your opponents backrow without them being able to respond to it in any way.

Raidraptor - Final Fortress Falcon : Unaffected by everything if brought out by ranking up or by Raidraptor - Arsenal Falcons effect. Pretty good boss monster to fall back on if things go wrong.

Raidraptor - Wise Strix : Probably the first monster you special summon from your extra deck. Lets you summon one lvl 4 from your deck, which normally lets you go into Raidraptor - Force Strix and by activating its search lets you add a rank-up spell to your hand, to access the rest of your extra deck toolbox.

 

Some final thoughts:

You might think about freing up 2 spaces in the extra deck, so you can add Zoodiac Chakanine and Zoodiac Drident . However since most Raidraptor cards lock you into only being able to summon Raidraptors, there probably won't be any situations where you can actually summon Zoodiac Drident . And since you need to summon Zoodiac Chakanine first and summon Zoodiac Drident on top of it, you cannot special summon it on your opponents turn with something like Wonder Xyz .

Foolish Burial is something to consider to replace a Raidraptor - Call , since by sending Raidraptor - Fuzzy Lanius or Raidraptor - Mimicry Lanius you can basically get an additional special summon too.

Monster Reborn is also an option to eliminate another Raidraptor - Call .

Rank-Up-Magic Soul Shave Force is also a consideration, but since Cyber Dragon Infinity isn't available, it doesn't seem worth it.

Raidraptor's Phantom Knights Claw , Raptor's Gust and Raidraptor - Booster Strix  are also worth considering if you want to turn this into a going first deck, maybe even Raidraptor - Readiness .

If you want to cut down on the amount of cards locking you into Raidraptors you can consider Simorgh, Bird of Perfection to send Simorgh, Bird of Protection to add Elborz, the Sacred Lands of Simorgh , to then summon Simorgh, Bird of Protection from the grave and normal summon another winged beast from your hand using Elborz, the Sacred Lands of Simorgh .

Another option to get around the only Raidraptors thing is to combine Raidraptor - Singing Lanius , Raider's Wing and Raidraptor - Strangle Lanius with Blackwings like Blackwing - Zephyros the Elite , Blackwing - Bora the Spear and Blackwing - Kris the Crack of Dawn to get more lvl 4s on the field and go into the Raidraptor - Wise Strix / Raidraptor - Force Strix plays like usual, with Blackwing - Zephyros the Elite being a prime target to special summon from the deck with Raidraptor - Wise Strix , since we're only interested in its GY effect and if you return a Blackwing - Bora the Spear you can summon it right back, since Blackwing - Bora the Spear isn't once per turn.

Seventh Ascension is also worth some consideration for some more rank up-spell searching.

 

I know it's kind of expensive for a deck that's not neccessarily that strong (seriously, without Raidraptor - Ultimate Falcon this deck is less than half as strong as it could be), but I find it incredibly fun to play, especially since every game feels unique with the numerous ways the extra deck toolbox lets you respond to the opponents filed.

Have fun and good luck in the festival.
